hile the men aim for their third straight.\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, the final round of the women's golf competition's takes place on Saturday, with live coverage beginning at 3 a.m.\", \"from\": 2319, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET on GOLF Channel and Peacock.\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two-time Olympic medalistLydia Ko(-9) of New Zealand is tied for the lead withMorgane Metrauxof Switzerland, while AmericansRose Zhang(-7) and defending Olympic gold medalistNelly Korda(-4) will look to charge up the leaderboard.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2520, \"end\": 2531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9956316776711979, \"rank\": 0.003187290327777104, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9912941525752187, \"rank\": 0.004630837021782268, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickherefor more information on tomorrow's coverage.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"***  Following are highlights from today's coverage of the Paris Olympics on the platforms of NBCUniversal:  TRACK & FIELD  Ato Boldon on the U.S. women's 4x100m relay team winning gold: \\\"The United States certainly had to do a lot of work on that anchor leg, but Sha'Carri Richardson was more than up to the task...when you have somebody with the top-end speed like Sha'Carri Richardson, she's able to bail you out of a lot of spots and she bailed the U.S. out to a win here.\\\"\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 3244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ato_Boldon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.28609107020019e-19, \"text\": \"Ato Boldon\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ato_Boldon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ato_Boldon\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999850915089079, \"rank\": 1.4701288996856841e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3031, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 3134, \"end\": 3154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boldon on Sha'Carri Richardson's anchor leg in the women's 4x100m: \\\"Sha'Carri had about two or three meters to make up [against]Rebekka Hassefrom Germany andDaryll Neita[of Great Britain], but neither of them could withstand the onslaught of Sha'Carri.\\\"\", \"from\": 3246, \"to\": 3499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3256, \"end\": 3276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boldon on the historic dominance of the U.S. women's 4x100m relay before the race: \\\"They can make the most mistakes because they always have the most horsepower\\u2026Even if something goes wrong, usually the United States can recover.\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3704, \"end\": 3717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999850915089079, \"rank\": 1.4701288996856841e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why they have won 11 gold medals in this event, more than any other country.\\\"\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leigh Diffey on Rai Benjamin winning his first gold medal in the men's 400m hurdles after taking silver in Tokyo: \\\"Karsten Warholmfalters!\", \"from\": 3817, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3817, \"end\": 3829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Diffey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leigh Diffey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Diffey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Diffey\"}, {\"begin\": 3833, \"end\": 3845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rai Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rai_Benjamin\", \"dbpedi